replies.body:
I don't know how meta this but this type of build is also quite fun to play with:
{{item:1412}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3053}} {{item:3022}} {{item:3006}}
You're extremely tanky, still deal alot of damage and you stick to people so well with the rage passive from triforce and the slow from mallet. The problem is you don't burst people that hard and it'a very upclose and person build since you need to be in range to use the triforce aa buff. This build works extremely well with fervor of battle or grasp of undying. Going either 18-0-12 or 12-0-18. This build is really strong at just fighting because you're somewhere between a toplane bruiser and a caster adc.

If you feel the game might take a while to ramp up then a more armour pen build is great for just bursting people down though and with this much armour pen
{{item:1412}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3147}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3071}} {{item:3006}} 
with this build you just burst people down so fast and so you'll want 18-0-12 with warlords bloodlust and the lifesteal from maw allowing you to act kinda like an ad assassin and your ult does crazy amounts of damage.
